(2714, 81492, '電子巴哈創意曲', '融合巴哈創意曲(鋼琴)與電子元素。\r\n可欣賞古典的小品，同時感受電音的氛圍，產生新的聆聽感。\r\n\r\n音樂有許多規則性，旋律所引動的內在結構規則，聲部的律動、對比、排列，和弦及節奏遵循著框架內的秩序。\r\n\r\n音樂可在和諧的結構中去聆聽，也可用對比的方式表現。正如同藍色放在白色、黑色或其他顏色下觀看，呈現的感覺會不同。\r\n\r\n一片聲音跟另一片聲音，可以疊合營造對比，兩者之間不一定要屬於同個結構規則，對比會創造出另一種聲響，產生另一種可能性。\r\n', '2010-09-20 00:00:00', 0, 2, 3, '崔', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-21 13:27:35', '2015-02-16 15:47:32', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2715, 1788, '青春潮夢', '當你待在自己的房間\r\n當你窩在自己的被窩\r\n當你帶起你的耳機\r\n當你看著自己做的夢\r\n當你和自己說話\r\n當你演著一部只屬於你自己的電影\r\n\r\n然後 青春的時光\r\n就這樣走了\r\n\r\n就像一場夢\r\n', '2010-08-21 00:00:00', 0, 2, 7, 'Sunny Charlie', '', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-21 23:12:59', '2015-02-16 15:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2716, 81711, 'Call It Blue (2010)', 'The heart. It''s where blues, jazz, rock, classical, metal and other types of music come together. It''s where the vision of new music is born. And it''s where the passion to create is ignited.\r\n\r\nOn a hot summer''s day on the outskirts of Takamatsu City, Tim and a friend were walking along an empty stretch of road when they came upon a most curious scene. Seemingly unrelated artifacts had been collected and arranged by someone with a beautifully artistic vision. And in the midst of it all was a bench. Tim sat down.\r\nCall It Blue\r\n\r\nAt this stage in his life, Tim is turning away from a product-centered focus, choosing a process-oriented path of creating the music that makes his heart sing.\r\n\r\nHis latest album, "Call It Blue", is a perfect example. Dedicating the month of July, 2010 to writing and recording whatever may reveal itself, Tim worked to keep his heart and mind open to the eclectic blend of styles that emerged.\r\n\r\nRefusing to follow the strict conventions that have driven the music industry for more than a generation, Tim remained determined to let this album reflect his actual creative process. The result is a snapshot of emotions and ideas... hopes and dreams... finish lines and skinned knees.\r\n\r\nHe realizes this may not please everyone. In fact, he understands it may not please anyone at all.\r\n\r\nHe''s okay with that, because he''s worked long and hard on this album to satisfy the inner vision that refuses to settle for less than his best. These seemingly unrelated artifacts have been collected and arranged by someone whose love and artistic vision guide him forward.\r\n\r\nAnd in the midst is a bench. Please... make yourself comfortable.', '2010-07-24 00:00:00', 0, 1, 14, 'Tim Birchard', 'Tim Birchard Music', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-22 05:27:23', '2015-02-16 15:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2717, 81711, 'Trip To Pine (2009)', 'Trip to Pine Production Notes\r\n\r\nMy brother Chris and I wrote these eleven songs over the course of 2009. He did the words, I did the music.\r\n\r\nThere are actually more than these eleven. A lot more. Versions that didn’t make the cut; ideas still simmering on the stovetop; songs that refused to play nice together, now relegated to ‘time out’…\r\n\r\nAll of them have taken me to new places within, bringing me closer to my brother. Deepest gratitude.', '2010-05-17 00:00:00', 0, 1, 6, 'Tim Birchard', 'Tim Birchard Music', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-22 06:12:43', '2015-02-16 15:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2718, 81711, 'Fancy Shampoo (2009)', 'A compilation of songs written from 2003-2009, Fancy Shampoo was completely written and recorded by Tim at various locations in Austin, Texas; Takamatsu, Japan; and Durango, Colorado.', '2009-01-24 00:00:00', 0, 1, 14, 'Tim Birchard', 'Tim Birchard Music', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-22 06:55:03', '2015-02-16 15:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2719, 81711, 'Songs for The Reverend (2007)', 'A featured artist at the prestigious Davis Gallery in Austin, Texas, painter Chris Chappell has been lauded by many for his sublime representations of everything from the magical to the mundane. \r\n\r\nNow his work has a dedicated soundtrack. \r\n\r\nWith "Songs for The Reverend: A Tribute to the Art of Chris Chappell", Colorado musician and Austin native Tim Birchard offers a glimpse of Chappell’s art, life and psyche through the lens of his music. \r\n\r\nInspired by Chappell’s rich portfolio and drawing from his own first-hand accounts of his friendship with Chappell that began in the late 80''s, Birchard offers a 12-song collection that weaves and staggers its way through rock, Indian raga, freak folk, jazz, country, psychobilly, metal, and classical neighborhoods, ending up, quite literally, at Chappell’s hall closet door. \r\n\r\nwww.chrischappellart.com \r\n\r\nWritten and recorded in Durango, Colorado.', '2010-08-22 00:00:00', 0, 1, 1, 'Tim Birchard', 'Tim Birchard Music', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-22 07:45:24', '2015-02-16 15:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2720, 81711, 'Dragonfly (2007)', 'Dragonfly is an eclectic collection of songs written and recorded while living in Takamatsu, Japan. Ranging stylistically from rock to jazz to pop to folk (and, in one case, rap), this collection provides a glimpse into a world of wonder, confusion, ambivalence, sadness and joy, all through a lens of optimism.', '2007-08-24 00:00:00', 0, 1, 4, 'Tim Birchard', 'Tim Birchard Music', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-22 08:11:00', '2015-02-16 15:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(2721, 745, '醒來', '黑色喜劇音樂來臨,黃藍白打頭陣作品! \r\n眾人皆醉時,黃藍白和你一起醒來!\r\n\r\n記得國小老師跟我們說過,每天最困難的第一件事情,就是鬧鐘響起後,怎麼說服自己起\r\n床... 「當你第一個念頭沒有打算醒來,你可能就錯過準時上學了....」\r\n\r\n沒想到這不止是在唸小學會面臨的事情,一直到社會上、也許一輩子, 也都一樣在每天,有著這最艱難的第一件要克服的問題...\r\n\r\n所以,醒來到底是為什麼?讓我們這麼不甘願、卻又這麼必然? 簡單來說,夢總是美好的,怎樣從睡夢中喚醒,總是需要一點勇氣或者時間的考驗。\r\n\r\n然而,醒來不代表夢的消失,他其實是夢的延伸、延伸到現實層面, 因為你清醒了,所以可以更勇敢的去追求你的夢!\r\n\r\n黃藍白的音樂,就是介於夢與現實兩者之間的,透過他的歌,可以聽到許多幻想與生活交織的故事... "你永遠可以作夢,不過請在打醒自己的狀況下,看見現實、勇敢追尋!\r\n', '2010-08-24 00:00:00', 0, 1, 5, '黃藍白', '我董娛樂', 0, '', 1, 0, '2010-08-23 14:29:58', '2015-02-16 15:47:33', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
